column1: Baby Barnaby's////I got the pink and white scramble (eggs+cheddar+ham chunks)
column2: she the green eggs (eggs+artichokes+some other greens). We each ate half of our plates and traded to be able to try everything. I would recommend the green eggs over pink and white because the latter
column4: was probably something I could make at home. The green eggs themselves had a creamier consistency that was unique and filling. Really good to spread over the dense toast that is served. Alongside the eggs are chicken sausage and potato cubes
column5: which are each also made well. I personally found the sausage a bit on the sweeter side but my friend really liked it. The potatoes were crisp on the outside and sandy soft on the inside.
